728786f-a.text:
618 Delafield Ave., east of the S.E. corner of Elizabeth Street. This mansion was, according to Beers' 1874 map, the home of O. Johnson. It belonged to J.C. Thompson in 1907 (Bromley map).
July 7, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
